author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
time required: 30 minutes
course: main course
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon}, 
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, 
~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, trim and thinly slice @button mushrooms{8%ounce} (skip if your 
mushrooms are pre-sliced!). Quarter @lemon{1}. Thinly slice @tomato{1} into 
rounds; lightly season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms, 
@paprika{1%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until 
browned and slightly crispy, ~{5-7%minutes}.

> For perfect timing, start mushrooms when potatoes have 10 minutes left!

Meanwhile, toast @sourdough bread{4%slice} until golden.

In a #medium bowl{}, toss @mixed greens{2%ounce} with a drizzle of 
@olive oil{1%teaspoon} and juice from one lemon wedge.

> Large drizzle of olive oil and juice from two wedges for 4 servings.

Spread @vegan mayonnaise{4%tablespoon} over sourdough slices. Top half the 
slices with mushrooms, tomato, and as much salad as you like. Close to 
form sandwiches.

Halve sandwiches and divide between plates. Serve with potato wedges, any 
remaining salad, and remaining lemon wedges on the side.